  "notes": "Wayuu (wayuunaiki) — Arawakan language of the Guajira Peninsula (Colombia and Venezuela). Latin orthography standardised for bilingual education. Six vowel qualities /i ɛ ɨ a u ɔ/ (⟨i e ü a u o⟩), each with a long counterpart written by doubling. Plosives and nasals lengthen (geminate), written double: pp tt kk mm nn. ⟨sh⟩ = /ʃ/, ⟨j⟩ = /h/, ⟨ꞌ⟩ (saltillo, also typed as an apostrophe) = glottal stop. Stress generally falls on the second syllable, with exceptions for long vowels and closed syllables.",
